grammar_point: まえに
jlpt: N5
meaning: The former ~ the latter, The first ~ the second
meaning_warning: null
details:
  Part of Speech: Case Marking Particle
  Register: Standard
  品詞: 表現
  単語の種類: 格助詞
  使用域: 一般
writeup: 前に is used when describing something that is either 'before something' (in time), or 'in front
  of something' (a location). It is used with verbs (in their non-past form), or nouns. When used with
  nouns, の is required before 前に .CautionAnother similar construction to 前に is 手前 に . 前に can be used for
  something that is in front of any location. However, 手前 に may only be used when things in front of you
  (or someone/something else) are being described physically.
examples:
  - japanese: 銀行の前にあるラーメン屋。
    english: The ramen shop in front of the bank.
  - japanese: 私の手前にある着物は高いです。
    english: The kimono right in front of me is expensive.
  - japanese: 食べるまえに「いただきます」と言う。
    english: Before eating we say 'いただきます'.
  - japanese: 帰るまえに勉強をする。
    english: Before going home I will study.
  - japanese: まえにここに来ました。
    english: I've been here before.
  - japanese: 食べるまえに手を洗います。
    english: I will wash my hands before I eat.
  - japanese: テレビのまえに、机があります。
    english: There is a desk in front of the TV.
url: https://bunpro.jp/grammar_points/まえに
false_friends:
  - term: あとで
    meaning: After, Later
    kind: antonym
  - term: 手前
    meaning: Before, In front of, From one's standpoint or side
    kind: synonym
  - term: ないうちに
    meaning: Before it becomes, Before ~ occurs, Without
    kind: synonym
  - term: 前者は・後者は
    meaning: The former ~ the latter, The first ~ the second
    kind: synonym
